com.twitter.elephantbird.pig.piggybank
Class ThriftToPigProtocol

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.thrift.protocol.TProtocol
      com.twitter.elephantbird.pig.piggybank.ThriftToPigProtocol

public class ThriftToPigProtocol
extends org.apache.thrift.protocol.TProtocol

Turns out this is not such a great idea, as the protocol does not get hit when a Thrift object field is missing -- it's simply silently dropped. This means for objects where an optional field is not set, all of the following fields will get shifted in terms of field order, as we can't use the protocol to insert an empty field.

Look out for a proper Thrift2Pig conversion using metadata introspection. For now, only use this when you know you don't have missing fields.

Author:
dmitriy
